## Required research steps

Assemble the review from systems of record, not from memory.

1. **Scorecard pull (`m365_*` + dashboards):** for each KPI in {{ persona.process_domains | join(", ") }}, pull current value, target, prior-cycle value, and trend from its dashboard. Link every figure.
2. **Cross-service narrative (WorkIQ):** sweep "what changed this cycle across {{ persona.process_domains | join(", ") }} — launches, incidents, partner milestones" to assemble the wins, the misses, and their causes.
3. **Partner-org status (`m365_*` + people search):** for each org in {{ persona.partner_orgs | join(", ") }}, pull the cycle's commitment status and resolve the named owner.
4. **Compliance posture (`m365_*`):** pull any control event, audit finding, or sign-off due this cycle; summarize and link — do not paste audit detail.
5. **Last review's asks:** check which decisions or commitments from the prior review closed, and carry the open ones forward.

Cite every number inline with its dashboard link. Never fabricate or round-to-impress a figure.

## Output format — the review pack

Save to `{{ "{" }}workspace{{ "}" }}/reviews/{{ "{" }}YYYY-MM-DD{{ "}" }}-{{ "{" }}mbr-or-qbr{{ "}" }}.md` and surface inline:

```
# <MBR | QBR>: {{ persona.org }} — {{ persona.first_name }}, <period>

## Narrative (3 sentences)
Outcome -> lever -> proof. The story leadership remembers.

## KPI scorecard
| KPI | Domain | Target | Actual | Prior | Trend | RAG | Owner |
|-----|--------|--------|--------|-------|-------|-----|-------|

## Wins (each tied to a KPI)
- <Win> -> moved <KPI> from <x> to <y>. <Source.>

## Risks & misses (every red or amber)
| KPI / area | Status | Root cause | Recovery action | Owner | By when |
|------------|--------|-----------|-----------------|-------|---------|

## Decisions & asks for the room
- **Ask:** <decision / budget / headcount / partner commitment> — **from:** <who> — **why now:** <KPI / deadline>

## Partner-org status
One line per org in {{ persona.partner_orgs | join(", ") }}: commitment, status, named owner.

## Compliance & control posture
SOX / Trade / Tax / Privacy / Anticorruption / Payments — events, sign-offs due, findings (linked, not pasted). If clean: "no open control items this cycle."

## Carry-forward from last review
Open asks and commitments still in flight.

## Appendix — sources
Every dashboard and document linked.
```

Render the readout deck with the PowerPoint (`pptx`) skill, or a one-page leave-behind with the Word (`docx`) skill; for a live, filterable scorecard use the Web Artifacts Builder skill.

## Run this as a Scout automation

Business reviews run on a fixed cadence, so set a Scout **Automation** (Automations -> New automation -> Schedule trigger) to draft the pack a few days ahead:

| Name | Schedule | Prompt | Scope |
|------|----------|--------|-------|
| {{ persona.first_name }} — MBR draft | First business day of each month, 7:00 AM | "Build my monthly business review." | Prior month vs. target |
| {{ persona.first_name }} — QBR draft | One week before quarter end, 7:00 AM | "Build my quarterly business review." | Quarter vs. plan; partner-org commitments |

### Heartbeat-safe behavior

When this runs unattended:

- Write the draft pack to the workspace and surface it; **do not** send it, share the deck, or take any approval-gated action — {{ persona.first_name }} reviews and presents.
- Show any unsourced metric as a gap to fill, never as a presented number.
- Keep labeled or Confidential control detail out of the body — summarize and link.

