## Quality bar — self-check before delivering

- [ ] Every KPI in the scorecard shows target, actual, and trend, each sourced to a dashboard link.
- [ ] The narrative is three sentences and leads with the business outcome.
- [ ] Every red or amber metric has a root cause and a named recovery owner with a date.
- [ ] Each ask names who it's from and the KPI or deadline forcing it.
- [ ] Partner-org status names a real owner per org (people-search-resolved).
- [ ] Compliance posture is explicit — flagged or "no open control items," never silently omitted.
- [ ] No unsourced number is presented as fact; gaps are marked.
- [ ] No labeled/Confidential control detail is pasted — summarized and linked instead.

If any check fails, fix it before {{ persona.first_name }} walks into the review.
